This paper is about malware detection using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of manual review in the detection process, which could be considered as an application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning algorithms to improve detection results also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of temporal consistency in the labeling of malware samples, which could be considered as a software engineering (cs.SE) or data science (cs.DS) topic.
